reviews.text: Very nice, up to date SEC campus with plenty of activities within walking distance that cater to the needs of students. Both a great place to get an education and have a somewhat decent night life. Would definitely recommend to others however I can only give it four stars because it does lack diversity and you can really 'feel' it in some locations.

Auburn University😄. This is the best place I've ever been to in my life. Auburn is not just a university, she is an alive being, she loves you from all her heart, shapes you and makes you shine like a diamond. There's just something in the air here that fills me with too much joy. I love Auburn as if she is my family. WAR EAGLE 🦅
"The university offers an incredible college and visitor experience!"
RTR!but I love the atmosphere of Auburn univ. it is so peaceful and I can just sit dow under a tree and cool off. Also the football stadium is very well done and perfect for auburn fans.
Nicest people. Beautiful campus.

I came to an Auburn game as a Gator fan when they played Texas A&M and was surprised how decent this stadium is. Is it as good as The Swamp? No.  Our seats were high up but they weren’t terrible. Had good line of sight during the game. We were in the A&M seats and their band was right below us and sadly we could barely hear them.  As someone who enjoys the bands this is disappointing. They should try and close in the stadium entirely for most seats and maybe an echo effect can help?  The fans were nice. No one shouting at me or A&M fans (I was wearing Gator clothing) that’s appreciated.

I always love to come here. Auburn vs. Alabama is a great show. It was the best football show I've ever been to. Great atmosphere. The stadium was clean. The staff were helpful and friendly. Beautiful stadium for a family trip. This is a great place for the whole family.
Beautiful venue! Super friendly staff, from the parking lot attendants to the ticket takers to concessions staff to security people. Even the crowd was great! Always love going to events here!

WAR EAGLE! The atmosphere is unlike anything, anywhere else. I absolutely love love love game day. Only down side, no alcohol sales in the stadium. I appreciate the family friendly environment they are creating at Jordan-Hare, however most of the fans have spent quite the time tailgating and "pregaming" and are already drunk. Maybe alcohol/beer sales could be regulated!
Always a great day when I get to watch the Auburn Tigers play. The stadium is efficient and the restrooms and vendors are frequent enough you don’t have to go far from your seat.

Staff was kind. clean and quiet.
Pizza was good but not perfect(I prefer crunch texture of dough). Appetizers are great. Tuna salad and fried potato tower(I forgot it's name) good balance of sauce and food. 
I enjoyed here. I will visit again
The wait staff there is amazing, they treat you like family. They have the best pizza in town, not to mention a whole menu full of other options as well. I highly recommend going there.

Food is always great. Tonight the hostess informed us she was sitting me and family in a “new girls section “.  The hostess was obviously overwhelmed. We said no worries. The service was real bad! As well as the other people sitting in here section. Don’t put a new service in prime time at 5 pm on a Saturday night. I still tipped  20%, because that’s what you should do if you go out to dinner.
Pizza is under-cooked. The crust is too soft on the bottom. To eat it you need to use a knife and fork. The slices will not hold up in your hand.

I have to say It was not my favorite. The food was okay but not worth the price. I got the cajun chicken and alfredo pasta. The sauce tasted store bought, the dish was poorly seasoned, and the quantity was just enough to keep you from starving. I know that people have bad days and I'm hoping this was just one of them.

Please read edit!!  The best burger around by far!!! Make sure you go crazy with the topping... 
                    !!!!unfortunate edit!!!!!              made our 2 hour trip to cheeburger first time in about 8 months. Complete change of menu. No toppings anymore!!! The once famous and fabulous huge burger with all the toppings is now just a 1/3 lb fast food burger. The super large fry is now a small basket.  While the burger was good, it isn't a burger I would go out of my way to eat. We have made this trip many times a year for 9 years. Can't say as I see us ever going back.

Absolutely delicious. Just be aware that on the new menu, the BLT is not a bacon, lettuce and tomato burger, it is a wrap/sandwich. You can always build your own burger to include bacon, lettuce and tomato. The Onion rings are DELICIOUS!!!!!!! The fries are good too. The restaurant also specializes in unique style milk shakes.
They are offering breakfast now and it's great.  "Make your own omelet"  and hashbrowns/eggs/pancakes plate with fruit are really good!

We aren’t from here and a group of 5 of us came in within an hour of closing on a business trip from out of state. We didn’t realize they were closing soon and they didn’t treat us like it either. We realized how late for them we came in ...shortly after ordering. We ordered big, our food was fresh, timely, accurate, and the service was fantastic. They kindly let us stay a half hour after close while we were mindful of not overstaying our welcome. Our shakes to-go were tasty, very visually appealing and absolutely amazing, big and quality was worth the price. Big tasty burgers, great apps, impressive list of cold beer. The onion rings are to die for. Very sweet service here. Thank you for letting us enjoy our visit!!!!!
96 Health Department score. Clean dining area and restroom. Delicious burger, served hot and relatively quick. Veteran discount given

Picked up some take out. I had the Mongolian Beef with steamed rice and hot & sour soup. The soup was delicious and on the spicy side. Rice was nice and fluffy and I asked for a little cup of the “red sweet/sour sauce” as I like to put it on the rice. They were happy to accommodate my request.
The Mongolian Beef was outstanding! It was still piping hot when I opened the carton at home. The meat was tender and full of flavor. Best I’ve had in town. Will definitely order from them again.

I have a very mixed opinion of this place. Im giving three stars only because the food is always great, fresh, etc which is why I keep going back. HOWEVER, the service in house is subpar. Staff always seems frustrated that you are there and it takes FOREVER to get your food. So only go if you are not in a hurry to be anywhere soon. As far as calling in, good luck. That’s hit or miss. Some days I can get an answer and other days I never am able to get anyone to pick up the phone, and yes- I am calling during their funky business hours. Also, if you call in, still expect it to take at least 30 minutes or more for your food to be ready to be picked up.
Food not to bad.
We love this place. Been following that s business for over 20 years.
Nice Thai food, and inexpensive.

Great service, yummy food and lot of variety. Unfortunately, our palate seems to find everything tasting the same probably because of the similar ingredients. Husband had ordered the variety platter and he felt everything although named different, tasted exactly the same.
Amazing customer service. Very fast service and nice Waiters. Very good food too. 5star
Salsa taste like watered down tomato paste. We got fajitas for two. It was enough food, but no taste,  very bland. Disappointing because we love Mexican.

This is the worst restaurant ever! I will never come back to this place their salad was like salt where I could have a heart attack. And then don’t fry the shell they are using store bought shells and dipped in grease!!! The worst it don’t even deserve a one star. The manager told me to get a chimichanga if my food is to salty and I want it fried... I’m completely disgusted and disappointed ☹️

Very good food and fast friendly service.  The place is clean with the authentic music.
We had #37 and "N" on the menu... Check it out!
Awesome place. Great choices for food. We had salads and pizza and we were very pleased. We were just visitors to town but would come here again on our next visit.

Probably my favorite pizza place in Auburn. The staff are incredibly nice and easy to communicate with. The pizzas are fantastic and unique and every appetizer is perfect for sharing or eating as a meal on their own. And it might have one of the best tap walls in Auburn, even better than the bars.
I really loved it. They have the spiciest pizza in town. If you are spice lover, don't forget to stop by Mellow Mushroom!
Food is pretty good. Waitress was sweet when she came to our table. She just didn't come very much.
Awesome place! And Bazil pizza was great! But Im so sorry for our server. She recommended our pizza. But I cannot understand that menus because of my english skill.

Atmosphere is great. The bonless wings were delicious but had to much breading.  We got water when we first arrived while looking at the menu. The lunch specials came with a drink but when we mentioned a drink the waitress said "But you already have water".  So that specific server needs educated a bit.  Would definitely be a place to try again.
Always awesome Place. Started going there when I was in college and every time we go back it's always a must stop the Chicago wings are wonderful. They also have a gluten-free menu which is great

I always love dining here. I have been going since I was a kid for kids nights on Wednesday including a piñata that we got to hit. The food is always delicious and warm and there is a wide variety of choices. I always love the hot club and loaded potato soup especially on cold days!

We frequented this place when we were students but hadn’t been back in ten years!  The food was better than I remember but the wonderful environment hadn’t changed at all!  It was great to show our kids one of our favorite places when we lived in town. And most importantly, GET THE FRIED PICKLE SPEARS!!!!

This place came highly recommended by friends. We ordered the hot pepper cheese bits. These were really good but weren't listed with the corn nuggets so finding corn inside was a bit of a surprise - still tasty though. Maybe he gave us the flaming nuggets instead? Not sure. We all ordered burgers. I got the Orange and Blue and it was delicious. Everyone was happy with their orders. My only complaint would be the "cajun" steak fries were more or less just fries with an orange powder. I didn't taste anything unique or spicy. They were delicious but not cajun. We were in town for Science Olympiad but if we come back to Auburn, we'll definitely eat here again!
